2026 Regular Session
SENATE BILL NO. 159
BY SENATOR WOMACK AND REPRESENTATIVE RISER
ROADS/HIGHWAYS. Designates a portion of Louisiana Highway 17 in Franklin Parish as
the "Sergeant Rogelio "Roy" Gonzalez, Jr. Memorial Highway". (8/1/26)
1 AN ACT
2 To provide relative to state highways; to designate a portion of Louisiana Highway 17 in
3 Franklin Parish, as the "Sergeant Rogelio "Roy" Gonzalez, Jr. Memorial Highway";
4 to provide for location and placement of signage; to provide for restrictions on costs
5 of materials to the department; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, Louisiana
8 Highway 17, beginning at the intersection of Louisiana Highway 17 and Lawson Road
9 and ending at Louisiana Highway 4, all of which is situated in Franklin Parish is
10 hereby designated as "Sergeant Rogelio "Roy" Gonzalez, Jr. Memorial Highway".
11 Section 2. The Department of Transportation and Development is hereby
12 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs of this designation provided local or
13 private monies are received by the department equal to the department's actual costs
14 for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and installation of each sign, not to exceed
15 the sum of seven hundred fifty dollars per sign.
